records.nl_statement: If $f$ is a continuous mapping of a metric space $X$ into a metric space $Y$, prove that $f(\overline{E}) \subset \overline{f(E)}$ for every set $E \subset X$. ($\overline{E}$ denotes the closure of $E$).
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Topology Filter Real Complex TopologicalSpace Finset
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_4_2a
  {α : Type} [MetricSpace α]
  {β : Type} [MetricSpace β]
  (f : α → β)
  (h₁ : Continuous f)
  : ∀ (x : Set α), f '' (closure x) ⊆ closure (f '' x) :=

records.nl_statement: Prove that if $V$ is a complex inner-product space, then $\langle u, v\rangle=\frac{\|u+v\|^{2}-\|u-v\|^{2}+\|u+i v\|^{2} i-\|u-i v\|^{2} i}{4}$ for all $u, v \in V$.
